column7: Going to/from work
column10: All answers are for my anticipated commute this summer, when I'll be working full-time in downtown St. Paul. The plan is to bike from my apartment to the nearest light rail station (U.S. Bank Stadium) and either lock my bike there for the day or bring it on the train for the 30-45 minute ride. I have a car but I like not having to deal with parking or contribute to congestion when I don't have to.
column11: I want my ride to be interesting, comfortable, and safe. It'd be nice not to have to travel as far, but not so short that I wouldn't get to see anywhere else in the city along the way. I'd also like to be able to commute entirely by bike, but that's not always an option.
